[{"location":"api_spec/farama/#Farama-(standard-RL-environment)","page":"Farama Gym Environment","title":"Farama (standard RL environment)","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api_spec/farama/","page":"Farama Gym Environment","title":"Farama Gym Environment","text":"For farama environments, we do not need a clock.","category":"page"},{"location":"api_spec/farama/","page":"Farama Gym Environment","title":"Farama Gym Environment","text":"using EnvironmentEngine\n\nenv = Environment()\nagent = Agent()\n\nobs_cache = CircularBuffer{ConcreteObservationType}(1)\naction_cache = CircularBuffer{ConcreteActionType}(1)\n\nevery(obs_cache) do obs\n    push!(action_cache, action_inference(agent, obs))\nend\n\nevery(action_cache) do action\n    obs = step!(env, action)\n    push!(obs_cache, obs)\nend\n\n\n\n","category":"page"},{"location":"api_spec/drone/#Drone-example","page":"Drone Environment","title":"Drone example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api_spec/drone/","page":"Drone Environment","title":"Drone Environment","text":"The simplest example that uses the environment engine is a single agent that interacts with an environment with an associated clock.","category":"page"},{"location":"api_spec/drone/","page":"Drone Environment","title":"Drone Environment","text":"using EnvironmentEngine\n\ninitialize_clock!(real_time_factor=1.0)\n\nenv = Environment()\nagent = Agent()\n\nobs_cache = CircularBuffer{ConcreteObservationType}(10)\n\n# Sensor frequency\nevery(1ms) do dt\n    push!(obs_cache, generate_observation(env, agent))\nend\n\n# State update as soon as observation is available\nevery(obs_cache) do obs\n    state_update!(agent, obs)\nend\n\n# Planning as soon as state is possible\nevery(asap) do \n    plan!(agent)\nend\n\n# Action execution on hardware limitation frequency\nevery(2ms) do dt\n    act!(agent, env)\nend\n\n# Environment update on seperate frequency (e.g. physics engine)\nevery(1ms) do dt\n    update!(env, dt)\nend\n","category":"page"},{"location":"api_spec/multi_agent/#Multi-agent-environment","page":"Multi-Agent Environment","title":"Multi-agent environment","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api_spec/multi_agent/","page":"Multi-Agent Environment","title":"Multi-Agent Environment","text":"using EnvironmentEngine\n\ninitialize_clock!(real_time_factor=1.0)\n\nenv = Environment()\n\nfunction add!(agent)\n    \n    obs_cache = CircularBuffer{ConcreteObservationType}(10)\n\n    # Sensor frequency\n    every(1ms) do\n        push!(obs_cache, generate_observation(env, agent))\n    end\n\n    # State update as soon as observation is available\n    every(obs_cache) do obs\n        state_update!(agent, obs)\n    end\n\n    # Planning as soon as state is possible\n    every(asap) do \n        plan!(agent)\n    end\n\n    # Action execution on hardware limitation frequency\n    every(2ms) do \n        act!(agent, env)\n    end\nend\n\nadd!(Agent())\nadd!(Agent())\n\nevery(1ms) do dt\n    update!(env, dt)\nend\n","category":"page"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for EnvironmentEngine.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.MachineClock","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.MachineClock","text":"MachineClock\n\nA clock that uses the system time. The time is represented in seconds.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.TickedScheduler","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.TickedScheduler","text":"TickedScheduler{C <: Clock, T} <: Scheduler\n\nA scheduler that processes jobs at regular tick intervals.\n\nFields\n\nclock::C: The clock providing time information\njobs::Vector{Job}: The jobs to be scheduled\nticker::Ticker{T}: The ticker that manages timing\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.TickedScheduler-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{EnvironmentEngine.Clock, T}} where T","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.TickedScheduler","text":"TickedScheduler(clock::Clock, tick_period::T) where {T}\n\nCreate a new TickedScheduler with the specified clock and tick period.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.Ticker","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.Ticker","text":"Ticker{T}\n\nA mutable struct that handles time accumulation and tick processing.\n\nFields\n\nperiod::T: The fixed tick period\nlast_tick_time::T: The time when the last tick was processed\naccumulated_lag::T: Unprocessed time since the last tick\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.Ticker-Union{Tuple{Unitful.Quantity{T, 𝐓}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.Ticker","text":"Ticker(period::Quantity{T, 𝐓}) where {T}\n\nCreate a new Ticker with the specified tick period.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.TimedJob","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.TimedJob","text":"TimedJob{F, T}\n\nA job that executes at regular time intervals.\n\nFields\n\nf::F: The function to execute\nticker::Ticker{T}: The ticker that manages timing\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.TimedJob-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Any, Unitful.Quantity{T, 𝐓}}} where T","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.TimedJob","text":"TimedJob(f, period::Quantity{T, 𝐓}) where {T}\n\nCreate a new TimedJob with the specified function and tick period.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.advance_to!-Tuple{EnvironmentEngine.Ticker, Unitful.Quantity{<:Number, 𝐓}}","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.advance_to!","text":"advance_to!(ticker::Ticker, absolute_time::Quantity{<:Number, 𝐓})\n\nAdvance the ticker to an absolute time, updating internal state accordingly.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.can_tick-Tuple{EnvironmentEngine.Ticker}","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.can_tick","text":"can_tick(ticker::Ticker)\n\nCheck if the ticker has accumulated enough time to process a tick.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.consume_tick!-Tuple{EnvironmentEngine.Ticker}","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.consume_tick!","text":"consume_tick!(ticker::Ticker)\n\nConsume one tick, reducing the accumulated lag by the tick period.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.global_clock-Tuple{}","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.global_clock","text":"global_clock()\n\nReturns the global clock instance.\n\nNote: This function is type-unstable but the type instability is isolated by function barriers in the calling code.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.global_scheduler-Tuple{}","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.global_scheduler","text":"global_scheduler()\n\nReturns the global scheduler instance.\n\nNote: This function is type-unstable but the type instability is isolated by function barriers in the calling code.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.now-Tuple{EnvironmentEngine.Clock}","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.now","text":"now(clock::Clock)\n\nReturns the current time in the clock using Unitful to represent the unit of time.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.progress!-Tuple{EnvironmentEngine.Job, Unitful.Quantity{<:Number, 𝐓}}","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.progress!","text":"progress!(job::Job, t::Quantity{<:Number, 𝐓})\n\nExecute the job with the current time. The job decides internally whether to perform work.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.progress!-Tuple{EnvironmentEngine.Ticker, Unitful.Quantity{<:Number, 𝐓}}","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.progress!","text":"progress!(ticker::Ticker, delta_time::Quantity{<:Number, 𝐓})\n\nProgress the ticker by a delta time, updating internal state accordingly.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.progress!-Tuple{EnvironmentEngine.TimedJob, Unitful.Quantity{<:Number, 𝐓}}","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.progress!","text":"progress!(job::TimedJob, dt::Quantity{<:Number, 𝐓})\n\nProgress the job by the specified time delta, executing the function for each available tick.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.reset!-Tuple{EnvironmentEngine.Ticker, Unitful.Quantity{<:Number, 𝐓}}","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.reset!","text":"reset!(ticker::Ticker, time::Quantity{<:Number, 𝐓})\n\nReset the ticker to start at the specified time with no accumulated lag.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.reset_global_clock!-Tuple{}","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.reset_global_clock!","text":"reset_global_clock!()\n\nResets the global clock to the default MachineClock instance.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.reset_global_scheduler!-Tuple{}","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.reset_global_scheduler!","text":"reset_global_scheduler!()\n\nResets the global scheduler to the default TickedScheduler instance.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.schedule!-Tuple{EnvironmentEngine.Scheduler, EnvironmentEngine.Job}","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.schedule!","text":"schedule!(scheduler::Scheduler, job::Job)\n\nRegister a job with the scheduler to run. Can be implemented for concrete types to define scheduling behavior for different schedulers and job types.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.schedule!-Tuple{EnvironmentEngine.TickedScheduler, EnvironmentEngine.Job}","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.schedule!","text":"schedule!(scheduler::TickedScheduler, job::Job)\n\nSchedule a job to be executed by the scheduler.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.set_global_clock!-Tuple{EnvironmentEngine.Clock}","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.set_global_clock!","text":"set_global_clock!(clock::Clock)\n\nSets the global clock to the specified instance.\n\nArguments\n\nclock::Clock: The clock instance to use globally\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.set_global_scheduler!-Tuple{EnvironmentEngine.Scheduler}","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.set_global_scheduler!","text":"set_global_scheduler!(scheduler::Scheduler)\n\nSets the global scheduler to the specified instance.\n\nArguments\n\nscheduler::Scheduler: The scheduler instance to use globally\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.update!-Tuple{EnvironmentEngine.Scheduler}","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.update!","text":"update!(scheduler::Scheduler)\n\nUpdate the scheduler.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#EnvironmentEngine.update!-Tuple{EnvironmentEngine.TickedScheduler}","page":"Home","title":"EnvironmentEngine.update!","text":"update!(scheduler::TickedScheduler)\n\nUpdate the scheduler by advancing to the current time and processing available ticks.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
